# API route user scoping

All API routes under `app/api/` must enforce per-user isolation.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD – resolve session, guard, scope query
import { getServerSession } from "next-auth";

export async function GET(req: Request) {
  const session = await getServerSession();
  if (!session?.user?.id) return new Response(null, { status: 401 });

  const items = await prisma.assignment.findMany({
    where: { userId: session.user.id },
    orderBy: { dueDate: "asc" },
  });
  return Response.json(items);
}
```

- Always call `getServerSession()` (or equivalent) first
- Return 401 if no session
- Include `userId: session.user.id` in every `where` clause
- For resource-by-id routes, verify `resource.userId === session.user.id` before returning; otherwise 404
